Pre-Game Insights: Netherlands striker Cody Gakpo believes there will be more space for his team to attack in the upcoming Nations League clash against Germany.
The Netherlands drew 2-2 with Germany last month in an open and attacking game in Amsterdam, and a similar style encounter is expected for the return in Munich.
Germany leads the standings on seven points, two more than the second-placed Netherlands after three games.
Virgil van Dijk will be missing as he sits out a one-match ban after receiving a red card in the game against Hungary.
Coach Ronald Koeman mentioned that either Stefan de Vrij or Denzel Dumfries would replace Van Dijk as captain.
